<p>Easton
                    School District is a rural school district located in the Cascade
                    Mountains. There are approximately 100 students, Preschool through
                    12th grade that attend Easton School. Easton School District is
                    located in Upper Kittitas County and the boundaries extend from
                    the top of Snoqualmie Summit to West Nelson Siding Road (Exit 74
                    on I-90).</p>
                  <p><img src="images/Allschoolphotob2009.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="205" border="0"></p>
                  <p>Easton
                    is surrounded by spectacular views of the surrounding mountains,
                    rivers and lakes. There are numerous year-round activities to
                    enjoy, including some of the best
                    snowmobile trails in the state, and the summer offers some of
                    the best outdoor activities in the county.</p>
                  <p>Easton
                    School has a caring staff and offers a small school atmosphere
                    where students actively participate and there is a high level of
                    personal interaction between the staff, students, parents and
                    local community. Easton School offers small classes,
                    personalized attention and extra support for early learners. We
                    offer preschool and full-day kindergarten, and
                    paraprofessionals assist the classroom teachers and provide
                    additional support to students in small group sessions.  Easton
                    School is able to take full advantage of the mountainous, outdoor
                    setting to bring valuable life-long experiences to their students. 
                    These opportunities include fly fishing and fly tying,
                    cross-country and downhill skiing, archery, geocaching and rock
                    climbing.</p>
